               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18451027-2174-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2174-18451027 t18451027-2174-offence-1 t18451027-2174-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>2174. <persName id="def1-2174-18451027" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2174-18451027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2174-18451027" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2174-18451027" type="surname" value="BERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2174-18451027" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ROBERT BERRY</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-2174-18451027" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-2174-18451027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2174-18451027" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2174-18451027" type="surname" value="M'CARTHY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2174-18451027" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">FRANCIS M'CARTHY</hi>
                  </persName> were in<lb></lb>indicted for<rs id="t18451027-2174-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18451027-2174-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18451027-2174-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> unlawfully uttering counterfeit coin; to which</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">M'CARTHY</hi> pleaded <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18451027-2174-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2174-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2174-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="pleadedGuilty"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 19.—</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18451027-2174-punishment-188" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2174-punishment-188" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-2174-punishment-188" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                        <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2174-18451027 t18451027-2174-punishment-188"></join>Confined One Year</rs>.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. SCRIVEN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">CLARK</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1245" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1245" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1245" type="surname" value="GOFF"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1245" type="given" value="CHARLES BURGESS"></interp>CHARLES BURGESS GOFF</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant L</hi> 8.) I was on duty in Walcot-place, Lambeth, on the 29th of Sept., with Brook—I saw the pri<lb></lb>soners—I had known M'Carthy by sight before—they were going in the direction of Kennington-common—I followed them through the New-road to Denmark-hill, Camberwell—they went down a turning leading to Camberwell-grove—I saw Berry go into a green-grocer's shop—I spoke to the female in the shop, and then followed the prisoners again—they went on to Cambcrwell-grcen, and stopped several minutes, and I saw M'Carthy give something to Berry—they separated, and Berry went into</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184510270203"></xptr>
               <p>Mrs. Godfrey's shop, which is a tobacconist's, and M'Carthy waited on the opposite side of the way—Berry came out, joined M'Carthy, and they went down the road—I went into Mrs. Godfrey's shop, and spoke to her—I came out again, and saw the prisoners in company on the opposite side of the way—I followed them to a confectioner's shop between the Green and Camberwell-gate—Berry went in there—when he came out I went in for about a minute—I overtook them again when I got to Wal<lb></lb>worth-road—when they got to Hampton-street they sat down, and waited four or five minutes—Berry then waited at the corner—M'Carthy went down the street, and took up something from the road, and rubbed some<lb></lb>thing between his fingers—he then joined Berry, and gave him what he had rubbed—they went up the road towards the Elephant and Castle-Berry went into Mrs. Cross's shop, and M'Carthy crossed the road to the opposite side—I saw Brook take hold of him, and I went into the shop—as I went in, Berry threw his head back—I thought he was going to swallow something—I took hold of him, and in the struggle I saw this shilling in his hand—I said, "This is a counterfeit shilling"—he said he was going to give 1<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for it—that was for the tobacco that Mrs. Cross was weighing—in going to the station, Brook was on ahead with M'Carthy, and Berry, pointing to M'Carthy, said, "That boy gave me the bad shil<lb></lb>ling"—the shilling I took from Berry had been rubbed with dirt.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Were you on duty? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, in plain clothes—I did not know Berry—I had been following them nearly three hours—when M'Carthy went down Hampton-street I was opposite the corner of the street—he went ten or twelve paces up the street—I was sometimes fifty yards from them, but when there was anything material to be seen, I got as close to them as I could.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1246" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1246" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1246" type="surname" value="BROOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1246" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BROOK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 118). I was with Goff on the 29th of Sept.—I know Mrs. Bicknell's shop—I saw Berry go into that shop, and M'Carthy was on the opposite side of the way—I was afterwards in the neighbourhood of Mrs. Cross's shop—I secured M'Carthy nearly opposite to it—I found these two counterfeit shillings in his hand, they are bitten and cut—he made a resistance.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1247" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1247" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1247" type="surname" value="GODFREY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1247" type="given" value="LOUISA"></interp>LOUISA GODFREY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of George Godfrey, a tobacconist, in High-street, Camberwell. On the 29th of Sept, Berry came to the shop for a pennyworth of tobacco—he put down a counterfeit shilling—I took it up, bit it, and said it was not good, and he went away without the tobacco—he said he took the shilling on the Green—this is it—I bit it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Which is the bite? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Here on the edge of it—I did not make this bend on it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1248" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1248" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1248" type="surname" value="BICKNELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1248" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY BICKNELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a tobacconist's shop in Regent-place, Wal<lb></lb>worth-road. Berry came there on the 29th of Sept for a pennyworth of tobacco—he offered me a shilling—I took it in my hand and cut two pieces out of it—this is it—I did not take it—he said I ought not to have done that, as he had just taken it down the road—he left the shop with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1249" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1249" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1249" type="surname" value="CROSS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1249" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH CROSS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of James Cross, a tobacconist, in Cumberland-row, Walworth-road. On the 29th of Sept. Berry came for a pennyworth of tobacco—he had not time to pay for it, as Mr. Goff rushed in and seized him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1250" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1250" type="surname" value="GOFF"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1250" type="given" value="CHARLES BURGESS"></interp>CHARLES BURGESS GOFF</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> This is the shilling I got out of Berry's hand at Mrs. Cross's.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184510270204"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1251" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1251" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1251" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>MR. JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Mint. These three shillings are all counterfeit, and made of the same metal throughout—to my best opinion they are all cast in the same mould.</p>
               <p>(Berry received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">BERRY</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18451027-2174-verdict-2" type="verdictDescription">
